<TITLE> EC commissioners to sit with govt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)Election Commission will sit with the government soon over the amendment to an article of the law that ensures an independent EC Secretariat, a commissioner said on Monday. The law gives singular authority to the secretary and chief election commissioner, but the 'commission' means chief election commissioner along with two other commissioners, Sohul Hussain told reporters. The flawed article should be amended, he added. On May 3, he termed the article 'against the constitution.' Chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda on May 7, "I don't want to work for nothing. If the election commissioners have anything to say about the free EC secretariat act, they should immediately sit with the government." "Giving statements in the media will not do any good," he had added. The commission has been divided over the power sharing after the law was passed in the first session of parliament. The two election commissioners have taken stand against the chief. bd
